Remote sensing which is carried out in Microwave region of electromagnetic spectrum is known as microwave remote sensing technique.
1mm to 100cm range of electromagnetic spectrum is generally used for spaceborne microwave remote sensing. Microwave region is in 
between Infrared and Radio waves.
Microwave bands are divided in K,X,C,S,L,P bands. There will be increase in wavelength of elecromagnetic waves if one will move from
K band to P band

SAR(SYNTHETIC APERATURE RADAR):-
SAR is a form of radar that is used to create images of objects, such as Landscapes - these images can be either two or three dimensional 
representations of object
SAR remote sensing is an imaging active microwave remote sensing technique which provides higher spatial resolution data.
