**************************************Comparison Of Various SAR bands*********************************************************


P-band :
Frequency: 43.2-438 MHZ
Wavelength(cm): 68.5-69.4
Spaceborne SAR Systems : BIOMASS
Applications: High Penetration, detection of target concealed by foliage or camouflage, buried object,archaeological, estimates of biomass, map forest
disturbances.

L-band :
Frequency: 1215-1300 MHZ
Wavelength(cm): 23.1-24.7
Spaceborne SAR Systems : SEASAT,JERS-1, ALOS PALSAR,ALOS-2 PALSAR-2,NISAR-L
Application : Good penetration, land applications-forestry, environmental monitoring,agriculture, geology, hydrology

S-band :
Frequency: 3.1-3.3 GHZ
Wavelength(cm): 9.1-9.7
Spaceborne SAR Systems : ALMAZ-1,HJ-1c,KONDOR-E,NOVASAR-1,NISAR-S
Application: Ship detection, ice-mapping, oil spill detection,flood mapping, forestry mapping,crop classification

C-band :
Frequency: 5.25-5.57 GHZ
Wavelength(cm): 5.4-5.7
Spaceborne SAR Systems : ERS -1/2,Envisat ASAR, Radarsat-1/2, RCM,RISAT-1/1-A,Sentinel 1A/B
Application: Sensitive to ocean features, ship detection sea ice serveillance, oil spill monitoring

X-band :
Frequency: 9.5-9.8 GHZ
Wavelength(cm): 3.1-3.2
Spaceborne SAR Systems : TerraSAR-X/TanDEM-X, COSMO-SkyMed,IGS-1B/3B,TecSAR,RISAT-2,PAZ,KOMPSAT-5,SAR-Lupe
Application: Sensitive to surface roughness, high resolution applications, topographic mapping, flood mapping.

